A) We assume in an EdgeR that there will be an appication in the remaining LExp. That might not be the case, thus creating multiple problems.
   We need to put an assertion that nun > unl

   This is probably not possible.


B) LForce might exist without the existence of an LLazyApp


C) Remove the unnecessary LForces LLazyApps in case of functions that return a Lazy type.


D) DO not transform returned functions into their result. Simply push the closure into a higher function and pass a pointer to the function that will create the closure.

